Concepts:
1) Subqueries : A subquery is a query inside another query. Theyâ€™re also called nested queries.
They can be placed in:
the WHERE clause
the FROM clause
the SELECT clause

2) Types of Subqueries:
| Type           | Returns                | Example                                                               | Used In       |
| -------------- | ---------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |
| **Scalar**     | Single value           | `(SELECT AVG(salary) FROM Employee)`                                  | WHERE, SELECT |
| **Multi-row**  | Multiple values        | `(SELECT department_id FROM Department)`                              | IN, ANY, ALL  |
| **Correlated** | Depends on outer query | `(SELECT MAX(salary) FROM Employee e2 WHERE e2.dept_id = e1.dept_id)` | WHERE         |

1) in -> atleast one value.
2) exists -> returns atleast one row -> a boolean check.
3) any -> greater than any value in the list.
4) all -> compares to all the values.

Practice Questions :
| Problem                                                                        | Title                         | Concepts Covered     |
| ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------- | -------------------- |
| [#197](https://leetcode.com/problems/rising-temperature/)                      | Rising Temperature            | Correlated subquery  |
| [#626](https://leetcode.com/problems/exchange-seats/)                          | Exchange Seats                | Subquery + filtering |
| [#184](https://leetcode.com/problems/department-highest-salary/)               | Highest salary per department | Correlated subquery  |
| [#183](https://leetcode.com/problems/customers-who-never-order/)               | Simple subquery (NOT IN)      | Basic nested query   |
| [#570](https://leetcode.com/problems/managers-with-at-least-5-direct-reports/) | Aggregate + subquery          | Multi-row            |
